24/03/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The foreign ministry issued a statement Tuesday (23 March), in which it welcomed the decision of Kosovo authorities to finance the repairs of Serb churches and houses damaged by last week's ethnic violence in the province.
The ministry also welcomed a statement from the EU condemning the violence and expressing the belief that political leaders in Kosovo would prevent any recurrence.
In other news, the EU and the UN signed an agreement Tuesday to start a joint project for asylum seekers and immigrants in Albania.
Building an efficient management system is a condition of the Stabilisation and Association Agreement with the EU.
(ATA - 23/03/04)
